Summaries for PTGES3 Gene

Entrez Gene Summary for PTGES3 Gene

  • This gene encodes an enzyme that converts prostaglandin endoperoxide H2 (PGH2) to prostaglandin E2 (PGE2). This protein functions as a co-chaperone with heat shock protein 90 (HSP90), localizing to response elements in DNA and disrupting transcriptional activation complexes. Alternative splicing results in multiple transcript variants. There are multiple pseudogenes of this gene on several different chromosomes. [provided by RefSeq, Feb 2016]

GeneCards Summary for PTGES3 Gene

PTGES3 (Prostaglandin E Synthase 3) is a Protein Coding gene. Among its related pathways are Linoleic acid metabolism and Metabolism. GO annotations related to this gene include unfolded protein binding and prostaglandin-E synthase activity. An important paralog of this gene is PTGES3L-AARSD1.

UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot for PTGES3 Gene

  • TEBP_HUMAN,Q15185

  • Cytosolic prostaglandin synthase that catalyzes the oxidoreduction of prostaglandin endoperoxide H2 (PGH2) to prostaglandin E2 (PGE2) (PubMed:10922363). Molecular chaperone that localizes to genomic response elements in a hormone-dependent manner and disrupts receptor-mediated transcriptional activation, by promoting disassembly of transcriptional regulatory complexes (PubMed:11274138, PubMed:12077419). Facilitates HIF alpha proteins hydroxylation via interaction with EGLN1/PHD2, leading to recruit EGLN1/PHD2 to the HSP90 pathway (PubMed:24711448).

Molecular function for PTGES3 Gene

UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot BiophysicochemicalProperties:
Kinetic parameters: KM=14 uM for PGH2 {ECO:0000269 PubMed:10922363}; Vmax=190 nmol/min/mg enzyme toward PGH2 {ECO:0000269 PubMed:10922363};
  • TEBP_HUMAN,Q15185
UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot CatalyticActivity:
(5Z,13E)-(15S)-9-alpha,11-alpha-epidioxy-15-hydroxyprosta-5,13-dienoate = (5Z,13E)-(15S)-11-alpha,15-dihydroxy-9-oxoprosta-5,13-dienoate.
  • TEBP_HUMAN,Q15185
UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot Function:
Cytosolic prostaglandin synthase that catalyzes the oxidoreduction of prostaglandin endoperoxide H2 (PGH2) to prostaglandin E2 (PGE2) (PubMed:10922363). Molecular chaperone that localizes to genomic response elements in a hormone-dependent manner and disrupts receptor-mediated transcriptional activation, by promoting disassembly of transcriptional regulatory complexes (PubMed:11274138, PubMed:12077419). Facilitates HIF alpha proteins hydroxylation via interaction with EGLN1/PHD2, leading to recruit EGLN1/PHD2 to the HSP90 pathway (PubMed:24711448).
  • TEBP_HUMAN,Q15185
